<TITLE> Manzur unveils election manifesto </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Chittagong, June 6 (bdnews24.com)  Mayoral candidate M Manzur Alam on Sunday unveiled his election manifesto at a press conference ahead of June 17 Chittagong City Corporation election. His manifesto contains 56 pledges, which he intends to implement in phases, and holds the slogan  'Change for a developed Chittagong'. Chittagong Development Movement (CDM) candidate Manzur is formally backed by the main opposition and the Jamaat-e-Islami. CDM convenor and Chittagong University professor Abul Kashem Chowdhury read out the manifesto. The short-term development projects include addressing water-logging problem, construction of new roads, spacious footpaths and flyovers, production of electricity and organic fertiliser out of garbage, and construction of sluice gates in different canals. The pledges also encompass adopting low-cost education projects, setting up of vocational institutes, ensuring transparency of information, launching city bus service, construction of prayer houses, eradication of mosquitoes and establishing gymnasiums. The mid-term development projects include setting up of homes for older people, reopening of closed mills and factories, ensuring citizen's rights for the slum dwellers, establishing drug rehabilitation centres, public library and renovation of city's stadiums. The long-term projects include construction of two bridges over and tunnel under the Karnaphuli River, hospitals and clinics, housing projects for the downtrodden, co-operative banks for generating self -employment, several five star hotels and entertainment parks. Moreover, extension of railway tracks up to Cox's Bazaar, assisting the government in implementing the deep sea-port, setting up of universities, city theatre centre, establishing IT village, launching metro commuter service and establishing city convention centre were also mentioned in the charter. bdnews
